- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The study uses thermographic images to train Convolutional Neural Networks for quality prediction. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of machine learning algorithms for quality prediction falls under this category. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper specifically mentions the use of Long Short Term Memory networks for training on raw signals. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): Although less likely, this category could be relevant as the study involves developing a process control system for improving injection molded part quality.
